<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="169" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d169">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72/4673½</note>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-10">
                                <hi rend="italic">10 May, 1917</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I think our list is now
                        complete, namely:<list>
                            <item>Mr. Elihu Root,</item>
                            <item>Mr. Charles R. Crane,</item>
                            <item>Dr. John R. Mott,</item>
                            <item>Mr. Cyrus H. McCormick,</item>
                            <item>Mr. S. R. Bertron,</item>
                            <item>Mr. James Duncan, as the representative of labor,</item>
                            <item>Mr. Charles Edward Russell.<note n="20a" xml:id="d169fn1">For the
                                    final composition of the Commission, see <ref target="frus1918Russiav01#pg_109">
                                        <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1918, Russia, vol.
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 109</ref>.</note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </p>
                    <p>I have only just learned of the willingness of Mr. Russell to serve and am
                        sending him a note today to learn the earliest hour at which he would be
                        ready to leave. I think it would be wise now to give out the names of the
                        Commissioners and supply the Press with as full information as they desire
                        about the several members. I am enclosing the account of Mr. Russell from
                            <hi rend="italic">Who’s Who</hi>.<note n="20b" xml:id="d169fn2">Not
                            printed.</note>
                    </p>
                    <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>